hkradial                              macro                             hkradial

NAME
     hhkkrraaddiiaall - scan along a radius in the HHKK-plane in reciprocal space

SYNOPSIS

     hhkkrraaddiiaall aannggllee ssttaarrtt eenndd iinntteerrvvaallss ttiimmee [[eexxpprreessssiioonn]]

DESCRIPTION

     The hhkkrraaddiiaall macro scans along a radius in the HHKK-plane in reciprocal
     space.  The angle of the arc from the positive HH axis is given by aannggllee and
     the scan runs from the radius given by ssttaarrtt to the radius given by eenndd.
     The number of data points collected will be iinntteerrvvaallss++11.  Count time is
     given by ttiimmee, which if positive, specifies seconds and if negative,
     specifies monitor counts.

     The optional last argument can supply expressions to be evaluated after HH
     and KK are calculated for each point.  You may, for example, supply an
     expression to calculate values for LL or include expressions to offset the
     values of HH and KK.

EXAMPLES

     hhkkrraaddiiaall 4455 ..00 ssqqrrtt((22)) 1100 1100
     hhkkrraaddiiaall 9900 00 11 2200 6600 ""HH++==..55;; KK++==..55""

SEE ALSO

